Package in.co.rays.proj4.model

Class FacultyModel

  • java.lang.Object
    • in.co.rays.proj4.model.FacultyModel
  • public class FacultyModel
extends java.lang.Object
    FacultyModel provides CRUD and search operations for FacultyBean against the database table st_faculty.

    It uses JDBCDataSource to obtain and close connections and throws application-specific checked exceptions to signal error conditions.

    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Chaitanya Bhatt

      • add

        public long add​(FacultyBean bean)
         throws ApplicationException,
                DuplicateRecordException
        Adds a new Faculty record to the database.

        Before insertion it resolves and sets college/course/subject names and checks for duplicate email and throws DuplicateRecordException if a record with same email exists.

        Parameters:
        bean - FacultyBean containing faculty data to add
        Returns:
        the primary key of the newly inserted faculty
        Throws:
        ApplicationException - if a general application/database error occurs
        DuplicateRecordException - if a faculty with same email already exists

      • update

        public void update​(FacultyBean bean)
            throws ApplicationException,
                   DuplicateRecordException
        Updates an existing Faculty record.

        It resolves college/course/subject names and checks for duplicate email (other than current record) and throws DuplicateRecordException if a different record with same email exists.

        Parameters:
        bean - FacultyBean containing updated faculty data
        Throws:
        ApplicationException - if a general application/database error occurs
        DuplicateRecordException - if another faculty with same email exists

        public java.util.List<FacultyBean> search​(FacultyBean bean,
                                          int pageNo,
                                          int pageSize)
                                   throws ApplicationException
        Searches for faculty matching the criteria provided in bean. If pageSize > 0, results are paginated.
        Parameters:
        bean - filter criteria; if null returns all records

        pageSize - number of records per page; pass 0 to disable pagination
